narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a course that goes broadly into the behavioral aspects of different topics in learning and memory. I would recommend it if you've taken (or are currently taking) another neuroscience class because there was a lot of overlap.
If you want a lower stress class that is still challenging and will teach not only about the brain but how to use it better to, and you like to ask lots of questions, this class is for you!
Take this class if you're interested in the behavior aspect of psych. The psychobiology part is really interesting, but limited as far as overall course material. Definitely a good class.
Definitely take it. The professor brings cookies!
